runConfirmationScript

public com.conceptwave.scripting.Object runConfirmationScript(CwObject wi,
                                                              CwObject order,
                                                              com.conceptwave.scripting.Object[] tasks,
                                                              com.conceptwave.scripting.Object[] orders)
It is invoked when user selected an operation on the worklist task, right before the Action script is run. The Confirmation script may ask for user confirmation before the Action script is run.

Parameters:
wi - If a single worklist task is selected, it corresponds to the selected worklist task (in other words, the worklist task on which the action is to be performed).
order - If a single worklist task is selected, it is the order associated with the current worklist task.
tasks - If multiple worklist tasks are selected, it is a list of all selected tasks.
orders - If multiple worklist tasks are selected, it is a list of all corresponding tasks orders.
Returns:
true or false, or string or object to display in the confirmation message box. If the script returns true, the worklist Action script is processed; otherwise, the action is cancelled.
